1
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,000
So tired.

2
00:00:24,340 --> 00:00:26,050
Time to get some work done.

3
00:00:44,020 --> 00:00:45,020
Growing a beard?

4
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:47,080
What about it?

5
00:00:47,940 --> 00:00:48,940
It looks good.

6
00:00:49,810 --> 00:00:50,710
Huh?

7
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:51,860
Nothing.

8
00:00:52,420 --> 00:00:54,079
Where are you now?

9
00:00:54,080 --> 00:00:55,080
Madrid.

10
00:00:56,060 --> 00:00:57,520
You're making me jealous.

11
00:00:58,180 --> 00:01:00,280
No wonder you have that rugged look.

12
00:01:01,720 --> 00:01:02,930
You think so?

13
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:06,920
Azuma?

14
00:01:09,160 --> 00:01:10,580
Seriously, I'm so jealous.

15
00:01:10,959 --> 00:01:12,239
I wish I could go there too.

16
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:14,840
Want to come?

17
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:16,860
Of course I'd go if I could.

18
00:01:17,540 --> 00:01:20,060
I'm not as carefree as some people.

19
00:01:20,820 --> 00:01:23,320
I don't have the luxury of
traveling abroad for months.

20
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:28,380
- I'll be back in the spring anyway.
- Spring is still a long way off.

21
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:30,000
It'll be here before you know it.

22
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,200
Easy for a traveler to say.

23
00:01:34,407 --> 00:01:34,957
So.

24
00:01:35,033 --> 00:01:38,043
You didn't just call to show
off your beard, did you?

25
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:39,940
No.

26
00:01:41,620 --> 00:01:42,960
The cactus I left with you.

27
00:01:42,985 --> 00:01:44,225
I wanted to ask how it's doing.

28
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:46,700
Asking about the cactus.

29
00:01:46,740 --> 00:01:48,020
As for you...

30
00:01:49,820 --> 00:01:51,420
Well, I can tell just by looking at you.

31
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:53,240
Well, thanks for that.

32
00:01:58,500 --> 00:01:59,500
Spring...

33
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:05,840
I've been waiting for spring.

34
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:47,999
"Life In Smokey Blue"

35
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,900
(Episode 7: A White Lie)

36
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:54,100
Takechi.

37
00:02:54,270 --> 00:02:56,119
What is it?

38
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:58,120
There's something I don't
understand in English...

39
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,080
If you don't mind, I can help you.

40
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:07,480
Tajimi-san has an urgent
matter and will be late.

41
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,620
It's fine. Any help is fine.

42
00:03:10,020 --> 00:03:11,520
Let me see.

43
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,900
Ah, sorry, sorry, I'm late.

44
00:03:16,740 --> 00:03:19,119
Oh, Takechi, you've
been studying hard lately.

45
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,220
Not really.

46
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,880
I'm preparing for my exams.
It's best to get a head start.

47
00:03:24,393 --> 00:03:26,233
You're already thinking about the future.

48
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:27,500
That's impressive.

49
00:03:28,912 --> 00:03:30,852
Well, it's for my own sake.

50
00:03:32,740 --> 00:03:34,439
What's that?

51
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:37,000
- That's weird.
- Oh, this?

52
00:03:37,780 --> 00:03:39,980
It's some clay my daughters
made in kindergarten.

53
00:03:40,050 --> 00:03:42,880
My wife turned it into a keychain.

54
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,390
It's funny, isn't it?

55
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,429
- I have to get to class.
- Hmm?

56
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:53,660
Right.

57
00:03:58,220 --> 00:04:00,800
Um, it's not that weird, actually.

58
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:03,210
It's pretty cute.

59
00:04:04,940 --> 00:04:06,010
Right?

60
00:04:11,850 --> 00:04:13,979
I thought Takechi was a quiet kid.

61
00:04:13,980 --> 00:04:15,639
Hard to get close to.

62
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:16,640
But it turns out,

63
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:19,080
he comes to ask questions
often. He's very dedicated.

64
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:21,179
He'll be a third-year next year.

65
00:04:21,180 --> 00:04:22,700
Maybe he's starting to get serious.

66
00:04:23,166 --> 00:04:25,856
And maybe... your teaching style suits him.

67
00:04:25,980 --> 00:04:27,030
I hope so.

68
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,799
Keep up the good work
with him, Azuma-sensei.

69
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,800
I will.

70
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:40,840
- By the way, Tajimi-san...
- Hmm?

71
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:44,399
Is it me or do you seem quite tired?

72
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,400
Ah.

73
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:46,780
Do I?

74
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:48,900
Ah...

75
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:52,660
Well, it's always a busy time of year.

76
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,360
It's a critical time for the students, too.

77
00:04:56,223 --> 00:04:58,865
We all have to work hard
and get through it together.

78
00:04:58,890 --> 00:05:00,080
Yeah.

79
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:01,800
By the way.

80
00:05:01,801 --> 00:05:06,000
I heard that in the lunar calendar, December is
also called 'the month of waiting for spring.'

81
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:14,710
I hope a warm spring
will come for everyone.

82
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,259
You say that like it has
nothing to do with you.

83
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:19,539
Hmm?

84
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:21,380
Now that you mention
it, I guess you're right.

85
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:25,240
Excuse me.

86
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:29,359
- Mejiro sensei.
- Yes.

87
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,880
About the translation here...

88
00:05:33,210 --> 00:05:34,210
Hmm...

89
00:05:34,860 --> 00:05:37,640
Azuma-san, your translations
are always very accurate.

90
00:05:38,820 --> 00:05:42,000
However, while being faithful
to the original is important,

91
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:43,620
it's a little stiff.

92
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:47,579
Perhaps it's time to try
adding a little more flair,

93
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:50,180
using more reader-friendly expressions.

94
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:52,180
Well, I'll be going now.

95
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:54,260
Okay.

96
00:05:54,550 --> 00:05:57,000
That's actually a compliment, you know.

97
00:05:57,420 --> 00:05:58,919
It means your fundamentals are solid.

98
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:01,360
That's why you're being asked
to move on to the 'next level.'

99
00:06:01,385 --> 00:06:03,564
Is that so?

100
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:05,670
You should have more
confidence in yourself.

101
00:06:05,695 --> 00:06:09,034
Azuma, your translations really have style.

102
00:06:09,230 --> 00:06:11,010
Thank you.

103
00:06:11,035 --> 00:06:11,645
For me,

104
00:06:11,761 --> 00:06:14,970
your words have always been a
source of support for me, Tajimi-san.

105
00:06:16,270 --> 00:06:18,630
The reason I decided to
become a professional translator...

106
00:06:18,990 --> 00:06:21,180
was all thanks to what you said.

107
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:23,590
Oh, is that right?

108
00:06:25,230 --> 00:06:26,270
I'm so happy to hear that.

109
00:06:26,870 --> 00:06:28,680
I never thought you'd say that to me.

110
00:06:30,570 --> 00:06:30,840
Ah.

111
00:06:30,841 --> 00:06:34,060
I remember, we were translating...

112
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:37,190
Auster's 'Ghosts.'

113
00:06:37,990 --> 00:06:40,721
That's still a very
important book in my life.

114
00:06:44,329 --> 00:06:45,709
Brings back memories.

115
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:49,440
That was 20 years ago now.

116
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:54,069
- Do you remember the first time we talked?
- Hmm?

117
00:06:54,070 --> 00:06:58,269
My classmates dragged me to a mixer,

118
00:06:58,270 --> 00:06:59,446
and you helped me out of a jam.

119
00:06:59,470 --> 00:07:00,829
You were a real lifesaver back then.

120
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:01,949
That time...

121
00:07:01,950 --> 00:07:04,330
I'll never forget the look
on your face, Azuma.

122
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:06,889
It was written all over your face:
'No! I can't take this anymore!'

123
00:07:06,890 --> 00:07:09,260
Hey, I'll never forget either.

124
00:07:09,530 --> 00:07:12,009
When I confessed I
wasn't interested in women,

125
00:07:12,010 --> 00:07:14,760
the indescribable look
on your face, Tajimi-san.

126
00:07:14,830 --> 00:07:16,570
Sorry about that.

127
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:19,229
I was trying my best
to keep a straight face.

128
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:20,200
A straight face?

129
00:07:20,201 --> 00:07:22,249
- Are you serious?
- Yeah.

130
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:23,630
That's impossible.

131
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:25,929
Not for someone as clumsy
and honest as you, Tajimi-san.

132
00:07:25,930 --> 00:07:27,510
Sorry for being clumsy.

133
00:07:27,710 --> 00:07:29,366
- I meant it as a compliment.
- No, you didn't.

134
00:07:29,390 --> 00:07:30,950
You've saved me so many times.

135
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:36,590
With your quiet, supportive kindness.

136
00:07:39,570 --> 00:07:42,360
I'm sure it will always be that way...

137
00:07:47,170 --> 00:07:48,669
Huh? Tajimi-san?

138
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:51,730
I heard he was taken by ambulance
yesterday and admitted to the hospital.

139
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,470
What's going on?

140
00:07:56,090 --> 00:07:57,290
Hey, Takechi.

141
00:07:57,630 --> 00:07:58,630
Here to ask a question?

142
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:08,290
Alright, let's start class.

143
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:12,129
Why is it Azuma-sensei?

144
00:08:12,130 --> 00:08:13,349
Where's Tajimi-san?

145
00:08:13,350 --> 00:08:15,350
I heard he has a cold
and will be out for a while.

146
00:08:15,610 --> 00:08:17,410
Everyone, please take
care of yourselves too.

147
00:08:27,470 --> 00:08:28,740
Takechi...

148
00:08:30,350 --> 00:08:33,710
I have something to ask you, sensei.

149
00:08:34,970 --> 00:08:37,490
If that's the case, go
back to the classroom first.

150
00:08:37,980 --> 00:08:43,020
Tajimi-san, is it really just a cold?

151
00:08:45,550 --> 00:08:46,810
Yes, that's right.

152
00:08:47,410 --> 00:08:48,619
It's that time of year.

153
00:08:48,620 --> 00:08:50,710
It would be bad if he
spread it to everyone.

154
00:08:52,230 --> 00:08:53,360
Really?

155
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:56,630
Yeah.

156
00:08:57,530 --> 00:09:01,540
But I've never heard of someone
being hospitalized for a cold.

157
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:06,040
- Sensei...
- Now, listen.

158
00:09:06,630 --> 00:09:09,110
As the saying goes, a cold
can lead to all sorts of illnesses.

159
00:09:09,370 --> 00:09:13,259
He was hospitalized just as a precaution.

160
00:09:13,260 --> 00:09:14,370
Don't worry.

161
00:09:17,070 --> 00:09:19,020
Don't make that face.

162
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:22,389
If my dear student makes a face like that,

163
00:09:22,390 --> 00:09:25,510
Tajimi-san won't be
able to rest easy, will he?

164
00:09:35,216 --> 00:09:36,569
[Facetiming Kuji]

165
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:03,369
Ah, it's Hara-san...

166
00:10:03,370 --> 00:10:05,976
(Hara Chibana: Here's a summary of yesterday's
class. Hope you can make it next time!)

167
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,540
(Azuma: Thank you.)
You're a lifesaver.

168
00:10:17,310 --> 00:10:19,170
How is Tajimi-san doing?

169
00:10:20,830 --> 00:10:22,890
I hope he comes back soon,

170
00:10:23,430 --> 00:10:24,889
but knowing him,

171
00:10:24,890 --> 00:10:27,889
he'd probably feel like
he's troubling everyone

172
00:10:27,890 --> 00:10:29,760
and force himself to come to work.

173
00:10:29,790 --> 00:10:31,090
True.

174
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:44,410
Kuji...?

175
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:56,060
(Merry Christmas! Wishing you a peaceful day
today and always, study hard! - Kuji Shizuka)

176
00:11:13,910 --> 00:11:17,149
That cold side of you
is actually kind of nice.

177
00:11:17,150 --> 00:11:18,410
Shut up.

178
00:11:21,090 --> 00:11:24,250
Thanks to you, I haven't
laughed like this in a long time.

179
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,070
You seem busy.

180
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:29,990
Yeah...

181
00:11:33,290 --> 00:11:36,650
Tajimi-san... he's been hospitalized.

182
00:11:37,823 --> 00:11:38,823
Is it bad?

183
00:11:40,090 --> 00:11:44,300
No visitors except family.
It must be pretty serious.

184
00:11:55,130 --> 00:11:56,810
Are you okay?

185
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:59,720
Yeah, I'm fine.

186
00:12:00,610 --> 00:12:04,550
Anyway, that's the situation.
I'm busy too, so I have to go.

187
00:12:05,330 --> 00:12:07,190
- Okay.
- Bye.

188
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:17,170
Um...

189
00:12:18,775 --> 00:12:19,975
Yes?

190
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:25,440
Please tell me which
hospital Tajimi-san is in.

191
00:12:30,260 --> 00:12:31,780
I understand how you feel,

192
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:34,080
but I really can't just tell a student.

193
00:12:35,540 --> 00:12:36,540
I know.

194
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:39,700
But,

195
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:44,190
at least take this...

196
00:12:44,859 --> 00:12:47,239
[A good luck charm for health]

197
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,280
A good luck charm...?

198
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:52,300
This is the first time I've
ever bought one of these.

199
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:58,140
I want to give it to Tajimi-san.

200
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:04,133
I... I'm so helpless.

201
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:07,410
It's so painful.

202
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,400
I see...

203
00:13:34,620 --> 00:13:36,120
How did it go?

204
00:13:36,820 --> 00:13:39,180
They're still not allowing visitors.

205
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,160
Doesn't that mean...

206
00:13:41,580 --> 00:13:42,990
It's pretty common these days.

207
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:45,700
They're being very strict to
prevent the spread of infection.

208
00:13:46,340 --> 00:13:48,890
It's not because of anything specific.

209
00:13:50,220 --> 00:13:51,220
Oh, I see...

210
00:13:51,940 --> 00:13:53,360
What about the good luck charm?

211
00:13:54,220 --> 00:13:57,530
They said they'd make sure he gets it.

212
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Thank goodness.

213
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:03,060
Thank you.

214
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:05,340
Thank you so much, sensei.

215
00:14:10,380 --> 00:14:11,580
I lied.

216
00:14:14,140 --> 00:14:15,420
Again...

217
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:18,450
And yet,

218
00:14:18,451 --> 00:14:21,089
seeing Takechi smile, even just a little,

219
00:14:21,090 --> 00:14:24,590
I convinced myself that was enough.

220
00:14:24,660 --> 00:14:26,530
It's so cold, isn't it?

221
00:14:26,886 --> 00:14:28,415
So much for 'the month
of waiting for spring.'

222
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:30,630
The real winter is just getting started.

223
00:14:32,020 --> 00:14:33,839
The month of waiting for spring?

224
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,800
I heard that's another name for December.

225
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:38,740
That's what Tajimi-san said.

226
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:42,380
The month of waiting for spring, huh?

227
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:47,550
I wish spring would come sooner.

228
00:14:50,113 --> 00:14:51,893
Everyone's waiting for spring.

229
00:14:53,526 --> 00:14:58,620
Hoping for it with all their hearts.
A spring that brings warmth to everyone.

230
00:15:00,907 --> 00:15:01,907
But...

231
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,860
He's just as I imagined.

232
00:15:35,927 --> 00:15:40,927
Tajimi-sensei must be a
kind and wonderful father.

233
00:15:43,820 --> 00:15:45,370
He is.

234
00:15:47,653 --> 00:15:52,553
A kind husband and a kind friend, too.

235
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:55,580
Yeah.

236
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:57,660
He's very kind.

237
00:16:00,406 --> 00:16:01,406
He was the same with me.

238
00:16:03,420 --> 00:16:06,620
He always made a point to talk to me.

239
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:08,960
It made me so happy.

240
00:16:10,540 --> 00:16:13,570
I even thought, how nice it
would be to have a father like him.

241
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:17,900
No, that's not it.

242
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:22,920
Whether I saw him as a 'father figure, '

243
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,180
or if it was something else,

244
00:16:28,140 --> 00:16:31,890
at this point, I don't even
know myself anymore.

245
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:42,970
The good luck charm didn't work.

246
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:41,420
I'm sorry, Takechi.

247
00:17:44,180 --> 00:17:48,160
It wasn't a sincere gesture, it was...

248
00:17:50,380 --> 00:17:52,570
I was just covering
things up with a little lie.

249
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:54,700
Pretending to be an adult.

250
00:17:55,800 --> 00:18:00,800
When really, I was just trying
to make things easier for myself.

251
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:05,650
You know, Azuma.

252
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:07,850
It was a white lie.

253
00:18:11,980 --> 00:18:16,090
'White lie'... a white lie.

254
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,360
It means a lie told without any ill intent.

255
00:18:22,820 --> 00:18:24,970
Tajimi-san...

256
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,600
Kuji?

257
00:18:40,460 --> 00:18:43,539
You could've at least called
to say you were back early.

258
00:18:43,540 --> 00:18:45,420
I figured it'd be faster
to just come see you.

259
00:18:45,790 --> 00:18:47,090
Oh.

260
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:51,060
Well then, wanna just go to bed?

261
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:53,839
This isn't the time for that.

262
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:57,270
There you go again,
putting on a brave face.

263
00:18:58,420 --> 00:19:00,920
It's clear that you're so excited to
see me after being away so long.

264
00:19:00,921 --> 00:19:02,459
Don't change the subject.

265
00:19:02,460 --> 00:19:03,759
Huh?

266
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:05,910
Don't try to brush it off.

267
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:13,166
You went to the funeral, didn't you?

268
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:15,520
For that senpai of yours.

269
00:19:16,980 --> 00:19:17,980
You know,

270
00:19:19,540 --> 00:19:21,890
are you going to go
through this all over again?

271
00:19:23,190 --> 00:19:25,559
If you let this break you again,

272
00:19:25,766 --> 00:19:28,336
you might not be able to get back up.

273
00:19:30,906 --> 00:19:32,876
You can cry for me,

274
00:19:33,706 --> 00:19:35,686
so why can't you cry for yourself?

275
00:19:48,660 --> 00:19:49,860
I'm so lonely.

276
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:56,160
It hurts so much.

277
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:00,830
He told me I had great taste.

278
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:06,180
That I was brilliant.

279
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:11,360
That's what he told me.

280
00:20:13,820 --> 00:20:15,580
The things I wanted to ask Tajimi-san,

281
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:21,580
there were still so, so many...

282
00:20:27,340 --> 00:20:29,500
From now on,

283
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:34,300
am I just going to keep going
through goodbyes like this?

284
00:20:36,386 --> 00:20:38,426
I act like I know everything,

285
00:20:40,180 --> 00:20:42,200
and I keep pretending to be an adult,

286
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,400
but when it comes to tomorrow,

287
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:48,380
or the future,

288
00:20:50,380 --> 00:20:52,950
I don't know anything at all.

289
00:20:59,340 --> 00:21:06,630
Everyone important to me just disappears.

290
00:21:12,393 --> 00:21:14,533
What am I even trying for?

291
00:21:16,460 --> 00:21:18,470
It all feels so empty.

292
00:21:39,780 --> 00:21:42,300
Good things will happen, too.

293
00:21:44,540 --> 00:21:46,540
Lots of them.

294
00:21:51,980 --> 00:21:52,980
Kuji.

295
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:55,980
Yeah?

296
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:01,480
Can you get me a tissue?

297
00:22:11,490 --> 00:22:12,530
Here.

298
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:22,660
Hang on, I'll make us something to eat.

299
00:22:29,210 --> 00:22:32,010
- I can't cook with you clinging to me.
- Keep it up.

300
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:33,900
Hey, you.

301
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:37,959
Grab this for me, and this.

302
00:22:37,984 --> 00:22:39,796
No matter how sad you are,

303
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:43,960
after you've cried and laughed,
you still have to eat.

304
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:47,260
Your cooking really is the best.

305
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:58,610
Those of us who are still
living have to keep on going.

306
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:02,559
(Next episode)
You went on a date last week, didn't you?

307
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:03,560
It'll be okay.

308
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:04,939
I'll always be here to protect you.

309
00:23:04,940 --> 00:23:07,980
I consider Hara-san a
very important friend.

310
00:23:08,180 --> 00:23:09,480
The feelings that connect us,

311
00:23:09,740 --> 00:23:10,580
I want to believe

312
00:23:10,605 --> 00:23:12,064
that a wonderful future lies ahead.

313
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:14,387
Stay with me. You can put it in.
